headline: Crucial Black Friday, AI bubble worries and Fed rate cut hopes
summary: Last week earnings results from retailers were mixed with Walmart (WMT) being a winner and Home Depot (HD) a loser. Russ Mould from AJ Bell believes that's why this Black Friday will be scrutinised even more closely. He also believes that despite Friday's bounce on Wall Street AI bubble fears haven't gone away but that rising hopes for an interest rate cut are justified. For more live coverage of the markets, watch the full episode of Market Sunrise and visit Yahoo Finance.
